Pour the @Water for the Rice{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting
lid.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once
boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still
covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve
(the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Cut the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g} into thirds. Peel and grate the
@Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and cut the @Lime{1} into
wedges.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the Tenderstem® and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}. Add a splash of
@water{1%splash}, then cover with a #lid{} (or #foil{}) and allow to cook until
tender, ~{4-6%minutes} more. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Remove the broccoli from the pan, cover to keep warm and set aside for later.

While the broccoli cooks, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%g} to a
#medium bowl{} with the @Cornflour{10%g}. Season with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Heat the (now empty) #frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.
Once hot, add the chicken and fry until golden brown on the outside,
~{6-8%minutes} total. Turn every ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.

In the meantime, in a medium bowl, combine the @Gochujang Paste{50%g},
@Ketjap Manis{25%g}, @Honey{15%g}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml}, @Tomato Ketchup{1%tbsp} and
@Water for the Sauce{125%ml}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Once the chicken is browned, lower the heat to medium, add the garlic and
stir-fry, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir the sauce into the pan until the chicken is coated. Bring to a boil, then
lower the heat and simmer until the sauce has thickened slightly,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir the broccoli through the sauce until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add a
squeeze of lime from a lime wedge.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the middle of the chicken.

Taste and season with @salt{} or @ground black pepper{} or more lime juice if
needed. Add a splash of @water{} if the sauce is a little thick.

Fluff up your rice with a #fork{} and stir through the lime zest. Share the
zesty rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with your gochujang chicken stir-fry.

Sprinkle over the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5%g} and serve with any remaining
lime wedges to finish.

Enjoy!